taxonomy: Bags, Wallets and Luggage/Travel Accessories/Swiss Army Knives/Victorinox Ranger Imprint Red Swiss Army Knife (1.3763.71)
review: Great deal at 40% off.
Package came clean and with original packing and oil. No damages to sleeve or did not find it used at all.
The original Victorinox ranger imprint of 'camping' on the plastic sleeve.
It is a 21 use, tools in it.
1) Large blade knife.
2) small blade knife.
3) scissors.
4) wood saw...this one even cuts plastic pipes easily.
5) metal saw with 6) metal file 7)wood file on each side and 8) a nail cleaner on the edge.
9) can opener with 10) small screwdriver which is useable on small Phillip head screws also.
11) bottle opener with 12) flat head screw driver and 13) wire stripper.
14) tooth pick.
15) tweezers.
16) cock screw.
17) extra small flathead screwdriver.
18) small chisel.
19) hook- parcel lifter.
20) awl/ reamer with hole.
21) key ring.
You can add later, extra purchase an fine flathead screw driver n fit it on t cock screw and you can also add t pin in t empty pin slot of t plastic sleeve below t cock screw area.

One of t most practical edc knife for a mechanic, DIY, car, bike, camping site, expedition, construction site....wish if they could have added t ruler on t wood saw...u can make it a 23 tool, by just adding two more off t shelf tools from Victorinox india at a little more cost.
Pros:
The sharpness of the Swiss blades needs no introduction.
Very handy and useful to have on outdoor trips.(I actually used the saw to cut off a small tree branch)
The Red body looks good and solid.
All the utilities comes useful sometime or the other.
Using it for over 5 years. Sharpness still same.
Cons:
Very sharp knife and utilities need careful handling. (I have got cut several times over the years).
A bit bulky to carry around.
Wish the price would be lower.

Had ordered the product on 31st October under the guaranteed delivery scheme of 2 days. Got the delivery on 12th October after following up with the customer care relentlessly for one week. The paper box containing the knife was already open and the knife had scratches indicating prior use and oiled something I know isn't done by Victorinox. The knife looked beautiful otherwise especially with imprints. Top notch quality from Victorinox yet again. I have 15 tool ecoline that I have carrying everyday therefore wanted to replace that with a classic

Its a very good knife. My first sak, as my previous experience with this type  was cheap and chinese, but have used a leatherman before. Good blade, sharp. Saw is also very good. The key ring makes taking the hook difficult, but not impossible. a bit thicker than the other models and a nice sold feel. Knife could be in the middle layer though
my first swiss knife. awesome. really sharp. a little tight to open as i dont have good nails. all in all its great.
name: Victorinox Ranger Imprint Red Swiss Army Knife (1.3763.71)
